# Edge AI Camera Drivers — Kconfig

menu "Edge AI Camera Drivers"

config EDGE_AI_IMX415
    tristate "Sony IMX415 V4L2 Camera Sensor Driver"
    depends on I2C && VIDEO_V4L2 && VIDEO_V4L2_SUBDEV_API
    select REGMAP_I2C
    select V4L2_FWNODE
    help
      V4L2 sub-device driver for Sony IMX415 1/2.8" CMOS image sensor.
      Supports 1920×1080 @30fps RAW10 output via MIPI CSI-2 4-lane.

      To compile this driver as a module, choose M here:
      the module will be called imx415_v4l2.

config EDGE_AI_UART_SENSOR
    tristate "UART Sensor Character Device Driver"
    depends on SERIAL_DEV_BUS
    help
      Character device driver that wraps a UART port for sensor data
      acquisition (GPS NMEA / environmental sensors). Provides
      /dev/uart_sensor with read/write/poll/ioctl interface and
      sysfs statistics under /sys/class/edge-sensor/.

      To compile this driver as a module, choose M here:
      the module will be called uart_sensor.

config EDGE_AI_GPIO_TRIGGER
    tristate "GPIO Trigger Driver"
    depends on GPIOLIB
    help
      GPIO interrupt driver that exposes trigger events via
      /dev/gpio_trigger. Supports multiple GPIO pins with
      configurable debounce. Uses tasklet for bottom-half
      interrupt processing.

      To compile this driver as a module, choose M here:
      the module will be called gpio_trigger.

endmenu
